cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.ETM 

This paper proposes a model for optimizing energy consumption in smart grid households with energy storage systems. The model involves intertemporal trading and utility functions, which are concepts commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization problems are formulated as geometric programs and linear programming problems, which are techniques used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the varying nature of energy requirements and market energy prices, which are topics related to computer engineering (cs.CE) and energy and power systems (cs.ETM).
